{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"799582ce-6a92-4c13-a9ef-891275d7d449","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest compatibility bridge by default.**\n\nIn 3.8.0, the SDK still shipped the VSTest adapter/bridge so `vstest.console` could discover tests. Starting with 4.0, the test project builds as a standalone executable using **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** exclusively — `vstest.console` sees no tests because there's no adapter to translate for it.\n\n### You have two options\n\n**Option A (recommended) — switch your CI to `dotnet test`:**\n```\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n```\nThis works natively with Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\n**Option B — re-enable the VSTest bridge** by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply one of these changes to your project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"81e6e549-464f-4cd2-a159-3c18cac34804","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a known breaking change in MSTest.Sdk. Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.x, Microsoft introduced the \"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" (also known as the new test platform). In earlier versions of MSTest.Sdk (like 3.8.0), the VSTest bridge was enabled by default, meaning `vstest.console` could still discover and run tests. However, starting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0+, the VSTest compatibility layer (bridge) is no longer enabled by default. This means that `vstest.console` cannot discover tests unless you explicitly opt back in.\n\nThe key change is that MSTest.Sdk 4.x uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform as the default runner and no longer includes the VSTest bridge/adapter by default. To fix this, users need to either:\n\n\nTo work around this, you can switch your CI pipeline to use `dotnet test` instead, which natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform, or you can re-enable the VSTest bridge by adding a property to your project file that restores compatibility with `vstest.console`. Let me clarify the version history here—MSTest.Sdk 3.x already defaulted to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with the `EnableMSTestRunner` property set to true, but the VSTest bridge adapter was still included. In version 4.x, that bridge is no longer included by default.","outputTokens":668,"requestId":"67C4:29F112:1CF8CC2:20A1D33:69FD5537"},"id":"7748b6f1-9f50-48e7-a32e-070272a2c996","timestamp":"2026-05-08T03:15:20.274Z","parentId":"ed80c08f-8cae-44b2-8f01-cb1386086666"}
